Note:
==============================================================================
ATTRIBUTE - Typed attribute values, validation, normalization (Tier 1)
==============================================================================

The element.runa substrate models an attribute as a (name, value, namespace)
triple of borrowed string pointers.  This module sits atop that primitive
layer and provides:

  1. A typed value system (Boolean / Integer / Float / Url / Color /
     Length / Token-set / Enumerated / String).
  2. Parsers that lift the raw string value into the typed value.
  3. Validators that check whether a raw value satisfies a schema
     declared by attribute name.
  4. Normalizers that fold case, collapse whitespace, and apply
     HTML's boolean-attribute presence semantics.

The schema model is intentionally pluggable.  Callers register a small
TypedAttributeSchema record for each (attribute-name, expected-type)
pair they care about; for everything else the attribute is treated as
a free-form String.  This keeps the substrate format-agnostic while
matching what HTML5 (https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/dom.html
section 2.3) and SVG 2 (https://www.w3.org/TR/SVG2/types.html) expect
from their attribute machinery.

Records:

  TypedAttributeValue (24 bytes):
    off  0  type_tag       ATTR_TYPE_*
    off  8  payload        boxed value (String / Integer / Float / 0)
    off 16  unit_or_kind   ATTR_LEN_UNIT_* / ATTR_COLOR_SPACE_* / 0

  TypedAttributeSchema (32 bytes):
    off  0  name pointer   (NUL-terminated)
    off  8  expected_type  ATTR_TYPE_*
    off 16  is_boolean     0 or 1 (HTML boolean attribute marker)
    off 24  enum_values    List of allowed values or 0

References:
  - HTML Living Standard 2.3 "Common microsyntaxes"
  - CSS Color 4 https://www.w3.org/TR/css-color-4/
  - CSS Values 4 https://www.w3.org/TR/css-values-4/
  - URL Living Standard https://url.spec.whatwg.org/
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/arithmetic_core.runa" as Arith
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/string_builder.runa" as SB
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/char_core.runa" as Char
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/color/hsl.runa" as Hsl
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/color/palette.runa" as Palette

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONSTANTS
Note: ============================================================================

Constant ATTR_TYPE_STRING as Integer is 0
Constant ATTR_TYPE_BOOLEAN as Integer is 1
Constant ATTR_TYPE_INTEGER as Integer is 2
Constant ATTR_TYPE_FLOAT as Integer is 3
Constant ATTR_TYPE_URL as Integer is 4
Constant ATTR_TYPE_COLOR as Integer is 5
Constant ATTR_TYPE_LENGTH as Integer is 6
Constant ATTR_TYPE_TOKEN_SET as Integer is 7
Constant ATTR_TYPE_ENUMERATED as Integer is 8

Constant ATTR_LEN_UNIT_NONE as Integer is 0
Constant ATTR_LEN_UNIT_PX as Integer is 1
Constant ATTR_LEN_UNIT_EM as Integer is 2
Constant ATTR_LEN_UNIT_REM as Integer is 3
Constant ATTR_LEN_UNIT_PCT as Integer is 4
Constant ATTR_LEN_UNIT_PT as Integer is 5
Constant ATTR_LEN_UNIT_CM as Integer is 6
Constant ATTR_LEN_UNIT_MM as Integer is 7
Constant ATTR_LEN_UNIT_IN as Integer is 8
Constant ATTR_LEN_UNIT_VW as Integer is 9
Constant ATTR_LEN_UNIT_VH as Integer is 10

Constant ATTR_COLOR_SPACE_NAMED as Integer is 1
Constant ATTR_COLOR_SPACE_HEX as Integer is 2
Constant ATTR_COLOR_SPACE_RGB as Integer is 3
Constant ATTR_COLOR_SPACE_RGBA as Integer is 4
Constant ATTR_COLOR_SPACE_HSL as Integer is 5
Constant ATTR_COLOR_SPACE_HSLA as Integer is 6

Note: Decoded color record (32 bytes): four Float64 channels (r, g, b, a)
Note: bit-cast to Integer slots via Hsl.float_to_bits.  Each channel is in
Note: the unit interval [0, 1].  Layout matches the canonical output of
Note: hsl_to_rgb and palette_lookup_by_name so those helpers can write
Note: directly into the buffer.
Constant ATTR_COLOR_REC_SIZE as Integer is 32
Constant ATTR_COLOR_REC_OFF_R as Integer is 0
Constant ATTR_COLOR_REC_OFF_G as Integer is 8
Constant ATTR_COLOR_REC_OFF_B as Integer is 16
Constant ATTR_COLOR_REC_OFF_A as Integer is 24

Constant TYPED_VALUE_SIZE as Integer is 24
Constant TYPED_VALUE_OFF_TYPE as Integer is 0
Constant TYPED_VALUE_OFF_PAYLOAD as Integer is 8
Constant TYPED_VALUE_OFF_UNIT as Integer is 16

Constant ATTR_SCHEMA_SIZE as Integer is 32
Constant ATTR_SCHEMA_OFF_NAME as Integer is 0
Constant ATTR_SCHEMA_OFF_TYPE as Integer is 8
Constant ATTR_SCHEMA_OFF_BOOLEAN as Integer is 16
Constant ATTR_SCHEMA_OFF_ENUMS as Integer is 24

Constant ATTR_VALIDATE_OK as Integer is 0
Constant ATTR_VALIDATE_MISMATCH as Integer is -1
Constant ATTR_VALIDATE_PARSE_FAIL as Integer is -2
Constant ATTR_VALIDATE_NOT_IN_ENUM as Integer is -3

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TYPED VALUE CONSTRUCTION / ACCESS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Allocate a TypedAttributeValue record carrying a type tag, a boxed
payload pointer (whose interpretation depends on the tag), and an
auxiliary integer used by length-typed values for the unit and by
color-typed values for the color-space identifier.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Layout.allocate 24 bytes; write the three slots.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Caller owns the payload pointer's lifetime.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "typed_value_create" takes type_tag as Integer, payload as Integer, unit_or_kind as Integer returns Integer:
    Let record be proc allocate from Layout with TYPED_VALUE_SIZE
    If record is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, TYPED_VALUE_OFF_TYPE, type_tag
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, TYPED_VALUE_OFF_PAYLOAD, payload
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, TYPED_VALUE_OFF_UNIT, unit_or_kind
    Return record
End Process

Process called "typed_value_get_type" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    If value is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with value, TYPED_VALUE_OFF_TYPE
End Process

Process called "typed_value_get_payload" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    If value is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with value, TYPED_VALUE_OFF_PAYLOAD
End Process

Process called "typed_value_get_unit" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    If value is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with value, TYPED_VALUE_OFF_UNIT
End Process

Process called "typed_value_destroy" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    If value is equal to 0:
        Return ATTR_VALIDATE_OK
    End If
    Let tag be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with value, TYPED_VALUE_OFF_TYPE
    If tag is equal to ATTR_TYPE_COLOR:
        Let payload be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with value, TYPED_VALUE_OFF_PAYLOAD
        If payload is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with payload
        End If
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with value
    Return ATTR_VALIDATE_OK
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: SCHEMA CONSTRUCTION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Allocate a TypedAttributeSchema record.  When `is_boolean` is 1, the
schema represents an HTML boolean attribute (disabled, readonly, etc.)
where the value semantic is presence-vs-absence rather than the
stored string.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Layout.allocate 32 bytes; write the four slots.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Caller owns the name pointer and enum List.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "schema_create" takes name as Integer, type_tag as Integer, is_boolean as Integer, enums as Integer returns Integer:
    Let record be proc allocate from Layout with ATTR_SCHEMA_SIZE
    If record is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, ATTR_SCHEMA_OFF_NAME, name
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, ATTR_SCHEMA_OFF_TYPE, type_tag
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, ATTR_SCHEMA_OFF_BOOLEAN, is_boolean
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with record, ATTR_SCHEMA_OFF_ENUMS, enums
    Return record
End Process

Process called "schema_get_name" takes schema as Integer returns Integer:
    If schema is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with schema, ATTR_SCHEMA_OFF_NAME
End Process

Process called "schema_get_type" takes schema as Integer returns Integer:
    If schema is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with schema, ATTR_SCHEMA_OFF_TYPE
End Process

Process called "schema_is_boolean" takes schema as Integer returns Integer:
    If schema is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with schema, ATTR_SCHEMA_OFF_BOOLEAN
End Process

Process called "schema_get_enums" takes schema as Integer returns Integer:
    If schema is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with schema, ATTR_SCHEMA_OFF_ENUMS
End Process

Process called "schema_destroy" takes schema as Integer returns Integer:
    If schema is equal to 0:
        Return ATTR_VALIDATE_OK
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with schema
    Return ATTR_VALIDATE_OK
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: PARSE HELPERS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Parse a NUL-terminated decimal integer (optional sign).  Used by
integer and length parsers.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Skip a leading +/-, then accumulate digits.  Returns 0 (and writes
ATTR_VALIDATE_PARSE_FAIL to out_status) when the string is non-numeric
or empty.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(length).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
No allocation; mutates only the caller's status slot.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "attr_parse_int_with_pos" takes text as Integer, start as Integer, out_end as Integer, out_status as Integer returns Integer:
    If text is equal to 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_status, 0, ATTR_VALIDATE_PARSE_FAIL
        Return 0
    End If
    Let len be proc string_length from StringCore with text
    Let i be start
    Let sign be 1
    If i is less than len:
        Let first be proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, i
        If first is equal to 45:
            Set sign to -1
            Set i to i plus 1
        Otherwise:
            If first is equal to 43:
                Set i to i plus 1
            End If
        End If
    End If
    Let acc be 0
    Let started be 0
    While i is less than len:
        Let ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, i
        Let is_d be proc is_digit from Char with ch
        If is_d is equal to 1:
            Set acc to acc multiplied by 10
            Set acc to acc plus ch minus 48
            Set started to 1
            Set i to i plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Set i to len
        End If
    End While
    If started is equal to 0:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_status, 0, ATTR_VALIDATE_PARSE_FAIL
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_end, 0, i
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_status, 0, ATTR_VALIDATE_OK
    Let signed be sign multiplied by acc
    Return signed
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TYPED PARSERS
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Boolean attribute parser per HTML Living Standard section 2.3.4: any
presence value (including the empty string or the attribute's own name)
yields true; absence yields false.  Because parse_value receives a
non-null string, we always return true here; the false case is the
caller's responsibility.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Allocate a TypedAttributeValue with type ATTR_TYPE_BOOLEAN and payload
1.  Returns 0 on OOM.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Caller owns the returned value record.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "attr_parse_boolean" takes value_string as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc typed_value_create with ATTR_TYPE_BOOLEAN, 1, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Integer attribute parser.  Validates and produces a TypedAttributeValue
whose payload is the parsed integer (boxed as the raw Integer value).
Trailing garbage is rejected.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Run attr_parse_int_with_pos.  If status is OK and end position equals
string length, build a typed value.  Otherwise return 0.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(length).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Null-safe.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "attr_parse_integer" takes value_string as Integer returns Integer:
    If value_string is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let status_slot be proc allocate from Layout with 8
    If status_slot is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let end_slot be proc allocate from Layout with 8
    If end_slot is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with status_slot
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with status_slot, 0, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with end_slot, 0, 0
    Let parsed be proc attr_parse_int_with_pos with value_string, 0, end_slot, status_slot
    Let status be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with status_slot, 0
    Let end_pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with end_slot, 0
    proc deallocate from Layout with status_slot
    proc deallocate from Layout with end_slot
    Let len be proc string_length from StringCore with value_string
    If status is not equal to ATTR_VALIDATE_OK:
        Return 0
    End If
    If end_pos is not equal to len:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc typed_value_create with ATTR_TYPE_INTEGER, parsed, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
URL attribute parser per the URL Living Standard's "valid URL string"
requirement.  Full URL parsing is the network primitive's job; here we
only validate gross syntax (non-empty, no embedded whitespace) and
store the trimmed string verbatim.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Reject empty / whitespace-only inputs and inputs containing internal
whitespace characters.  Otherwise return the typed-value record
carrying the original string pointer.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(length).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
The URL is not normalized here; callers needing canonical form must
post-process.  No allocation beyond the typed-value record.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "attr_parse_url" takes value_string as Integer returns Integer:
    If value_string is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let len be proc string_length from StringCore with value_string
    If len is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than len:
        Let ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with value_string, i
        Let is_ws be proc is_whitespace from Char with ch
        If is_ws is equal to 1:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return proc typed_value_create with ATTR_TYPE_URL, value_string, 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Color-attribute parser supporting #rgb, #rgba, #rrggbb, #rrggbbaa,
rgb() / rgba() / hsl() / hsla() functional forms, and CSS Color Module
Level 4 named colors.  Eagerly decodes each form into a 32-byte record
holding four Float64 channels (r, g, b, a in [0, 1]) which becomes the
typed value's payload; the color space tag remains in the unit slot so
consumers can recover the original form.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
1. If first char is '#': parse 3 / 4 / 6 / 8 hex digits and write the
   per-channel values directly.
2. If starts with "rgb(" / "rgba(": parse the inner CSV (decimal 0..255
   or percentage 0..100%, alpha 0..1) and write channel floats.
3. If starts with "hsl(" / "hsla(": parse hue (degrees), saturation
   (percent), lightness (percent), and convert via Hsl.hsl_to_rgb.
4. Otherwise: look the identifier up in the CSS named-color palette
   via Palette.palette_lookup_by_name.
The 32-byte payload buffer is allocated on the owned heap; ownership
transfers to the returned TypedAttributeValue.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(length).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure or unrecognised input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "attr_is_hex_color" takes value_string as Integer returns Integer:
    Let len be proc string_length from StringCore with value_string
    If len is less than 4:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let first be proc string_char_at from StringCore with value_string, 0
    If first is not equal to 35:
        Return 0
    End If
    If len is not equal to 4:
        If len is not equal to 5:
            If len is not equal to 7:
                If len is not equal to 9:
                    Return 0
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If
    Let i be 1
    While i is less than len:
        Let ch be proc string_char_at from StringCore with value_string, i
        Let is_h be proc is_hex_digit from Char with ch
        If is_h is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Convert a single ASCII hex digit ('0'..'9', 'a'..'f', 'A'..'F') to its
numeric value 0..15.  Returns -1 if the character is not a hex digit.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
ASCII range tests.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Pure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "attr_hex_digit_value" takes ch as Integer returns Integer:
    If ch is greater than or equal to 48:
        If ch is less than or equal to 57:
            Return ch minus 48
        End If
    End If
    If ch is greater than or equal to 97:
        If ch is less than or equal to 102:
            Return (ch minus 97) plus 10
        End If
    End If
    If ch is greater than or equal to 65:
        If ch is less than or equal to 70:
            Return (ch minus 65) plus 10
        End If
    End If
    Return -1
End Process

@Reasoning
Allocate and zero-initialize a 32-byte color record holding four
Float64 channels (r, g, b, a) all set to 0.0.  Used as the payload
backing every decoded TypedAttributeValue of type ATTR_TYPE_COLOR.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Layout.allocate 32 bytes; for each of the four offsets, bit-cast 0.0
via Hsl.float_to_bits and write it via Memory.memory_set_int64.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Caller owns the returned record.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "attr_color_rec_alloc" returns Integer:
    Let rec be proc allocate from Layout with ATTR_COLOR_REC_SIZE
    If rec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let zero_bits be proc float_to_bits from Hsl with 0.0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with rec, ATTR_COLOR_REC_OFF_R, zero_bits
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with rec, ATTR_COLOR_REC_OFF_G, zero_bits
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with rec, ATTR_COLOR_REC_OFF_B, zero_bits
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with rec, ATTR_COLOR_REC_OFF_A, zero_bits
    Return rec
End Process

@Reasoning
Write a Float64 channel value at the given byte offset within an
already-allocated color record.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Bit-cast via Hsl.float_to_bits, then Memory.memory_set_int64.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Caller guarantees rec is a valid 32-byte color record.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "attr_color_rec_store" takes rec as Integer, offset as Integer, value as Float returns Integer:
    Let bits be proc float_to_bits from Hsl with value
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with rec, offset, bits
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Decode a #-prefixed hex color of length 4 (#rgb), 5 (#rgba), 7
(#rrggbb), or 9 (#rrggbbaa) into a freshly allocated color record.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
1. Determine the per-channel digit count (1 or 2) from the string
   length.
2. For each channel, read the digit(s), expand single-digit forms by
   nibble duplication (CSS Color 4 section 4.3), divide by 255 to map
   into the unit interval, and store via attr_color_rec_store.
3. The alpha channel defaults to 1.0 when not present.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(channel count).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure or malformed input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "attr_decode_hex_color" takes value_string as Integer returns Integer:
    Let len be proc string_length from StringCore with value_string
    Let digits_per_channel be 0
    Let has_alpha be 0
    If len is equal to 4:
        Set digits_per_channel to 1
    End If
    If len is equal to 5:
        Set digits_per_channel to 1
        Set has_alpha to 1
    End If
    If len is equal to 7:
        Set digits_per_channel to 2
    End If
    If len is equal to 9:
        Set digits_per_channel to 2
        Set has_alpha to 1
    End If
    If digits_per_channel is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let rec be proc attr_color_rec_alloc
    If rec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let channel_count be 3
    If has_alpha is equal to 1:
        Set channel_count to 4
    End If
    Let denom be proc int_to_float from Arith with 255
    Let pos be 1
    Let ci be 0
    While ci is less than channel_count:
        Let raw be 0
        If digits_per_channel is equal to 1:
            Let c1 be proc string_char_at from StringCore with value_string, pos
            Let v1 be proc attr_hex_digit_value with c1
            If v1 is less than 0:
                proc deallocate from Layout with rec
                Return 0
            End If
            Set raw to (v1 multiplied by 16) plus v1
            Set pos to pos plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Let c_hi be proc string_char_at from StringCore with value_string, pos
            Let c_lo be proc string_char_at from StringCore with value_string, pos plus 1
            Let v_hi be proc attr_hex_digit_value with c_hi
            Let v_lo be proc attr_hex_digit_value with c_lo
            If v_hi is less than 0:
                proc deallocate from Layout with rec
                Return 0
            End If
            If v_lo is less than 0:
                proc deallocate from Layout with rec
                Return 0
            End If
            Set raw to (v_hi multiplied by 16) plus v_lo
            Set pos to pos plus 2
        End If
        Let numer be proc int_to_float from Arith with raw
        Let channel be numer divided by denom
        Let off be 0
        If ci is equal to 0:
            Set off to ATTR_COLOR_REC_OFF_R
        End If
        If ci is equal to 1:
            Set off to ATTR_COLOR_REC_OFF_G
        End If
        If ci is equal to 2:
            Set off to ATTR_COLOR_REC_OFF_B
        End If
        If ci is equal to 3:
            Set off to ATTR_COLOR_REC_OFF_A
        End If
        proc attr_color_rec_store with rec, off, channel
        Set ci to ci plus 1
    End While
    If has_alpha is equal to 0:
        proc attr_color_rec_store with rec, ATTR_COLOR_REC_OFF_A, 1.0
    End If
    Return rec
End Process

@Reasoning
Skip ASCII whitespace starting at pos within the value_string and
return the first non-whitespace position (or len if the rest is all
whitespace).
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Loop while is_whitespace.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(length).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Pure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "attr_color_skip_ws" takes text as Integer, pos as Integer, len as Integer returns Integer:
    Let p be pos
    While p is less than len:
        Let c be proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, p
        Let ws be proc is_whitespace from Char with c
        If ws is equal to 1:
            Set p to p plus 1
        Otherwise:
            Return p
        End If
    End While
    Return p
End Process

@Reasoning
Parse a non-negative decimal number (with optional fractional part) at
the given position.  Writes the new position into out_end and returns
the parsed value as a Float64.  On failure writes pos unchanged into
out_end.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Accumulate integer digits into an Integer running total, then if a '.'
is encountered accumulate fractional digits with a divisor.  Convert to
Float via Arith.int_to_float and combine.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(digit count).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Pure; out_end caller-owned 8-byte slot.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "attr_color_read_number" takes text as Integer, pos as Integer, len as Integer, out_end as Integer returns Float:
    Let p be pos
    Let int_part be 0
    Let any_digits be 0
    Let done be 0
    While done is equal to 0:
        If p is greater than or equal to len:
            Set done to 1
        Otherwise:
            Let c be proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, p
            Let isd be proc is_digit from Char with c
            If isd is equal to 1:
                Set int_part to (int_part multiplied by 10) plus (c minus 48)
                Set any_digits to 1
                Set p to p plus 1
            Otherwise:
                Set done to 1
            End If
        End If
    End While
    Let total be proc int_to_float from Arith with int_part
    If p is less than len:
        Let dot be proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, p
        If dot is equal to 46:
            Set p to p plus 1
            Let frac_part be 0
            Let frac_scale be 1
            Let frac_done be 0
            While frac_done is equal to 0:
                If p is greater than or equal to len:
                    Set frac_done to 1
                Otherwise:
                    Let cf be proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, p
                    Let isdf be proc is_digit from Char with cf
                    If isdf is equal to 1:
                        Set frac_part to (frac_part multiplied by 10) plus (cf minus 48)
                        Set frac_scale to frac_scale multiplied by 10
                        Set any_digits to 1
                        Set p to p plus 1
                    Otherwise:
                        Set frac_done to 1
                    End If
                End If
            End While
            If frac_scale is greater than 1:
                Let frac_val be proc int_to_float from Arith with frac_part
                Let scale_val be proc int_to_float from Arith with frac_scale
                Set total to total plus (frac_val divided by scale_val)
            End If
        End If
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_end, 0, p
    If any_digits is equal to 0:
        Return 0.0
    End If
    Return total
End Process

@Reasoning
Skip a single literal character at pos if it matches expected; return
the new position.  Whitespace is skipped before the test.  Returns -1
when the expected character is not found.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Skip whitespace; compare character; return advanced position or -1.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Pure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "attr_color_expect_char" takes text as Integer, pos as Integer, len as Integer, expected as Integer returns Integer:
    Let p be proc attr_color_skip_ws with text, pos, len
    If p is greater than or equal to len:
        Return -1
    End If
    Let c be proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, p
    If c is not equal to expected:
        Return -1
    End If
    Return p plus 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Read one rgb / rgba channel.  CSS Color 4 allows integer (0..255) and
percentage (0..100%) forms.  Returns the value in [0, 1] and writes
the new position.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Skip whitespace; parse the numeric prefix; if followed by '%' divide
by 100.0, otherwise divide by 255.0.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(digit count).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Returns -1.0 on parse failure, with out_end left at the pre-parse
position.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "attr_color_read_rgb_channel" takes text as Integer, pos as Integer, len as Integer, out_end as Integer returns Float:
    Let after_ws be proc attr_color_skip_ws with text, pos, len
    Let n be proc attr_color_read_number with text, after_ws, len, out_end
    Let new_pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with out_end, 0
    If new_pos is equal to after_ws:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_end, 0, pos
        Return 0.0 minus 1.0
    End If
    If new_pos is less than len:
        Let nx be proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, new_pos
        If nx is equal to 37:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_end, 0, new_pos plus 1
            Let denom_pct be proc int_to_float from Arith with 100
            Return n divided by denom_pct
        End If
    End If
    Let denom be proc int_to_float from Arith with 255
    Return n divided by denom
End Process

@Reasoning
Read one alpha channel.  CSS Color 4 accepts a value 0..1 or 0..100%.
Returns the value in [0, 1] and writes the new position.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Skip whitespace; parse number; if followed by '%' divide by 100.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(digit count).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Returns -1.0 on parse failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "attr_color_read_alpha" takes text as Integer, pos as Integer, len as Integer, out_end as Integer returns Float:
    Let after_ws be proc attr_color_skip_ws with text, pos, len
    Let n be proc attr_color_read_number with text, after_ws, len, out_end
    Let new_pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with out_end, 0
    If new_pos is equal to after_ws:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_end, 0, pos
        Return 0.0 minus 1.0
    End If
    If new_pos is less than len:
        Let nx be proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, new_pos
        If nx is equal to 37:
            proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_end, 0, new_pos plus 1
            Let denom_pct be proc int_to_float from Arith with 100
            Return n divided by denom_pct
        End If
    End If
    Return n
End Process

@Reasoning
Read a percentage-typed value (0..100%) and return the value in
[0, 1].
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Skip whitespace; parse number; require trailing '%'; divide by 100.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(digit count).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Returns -1.0 on parse failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "attr_color_read_percent" takes text as Integer, pos as Integer, len as Integer, out_end as Integer returns Float:
    Let after_ws be proc attr_color_skip_ws with text, pos, len
    Let n be proc attr_color_read_number with text, after_ws, len, out_end
    Let new_pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with out_end, 0
    If new_pos is equal to after_ws:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_end, 0, pos
        Return 0.0 minus 1.0
    End If
    If new_pos is greater than or equal to len:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_end, 0, pos
        Return 0.0 minus 1.0
    End If
    Let nx be proc string_char_at from StringCore with text, new_pos
    If nx is not equal to 37:
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_end, 0, pos
        Return 0.0 minus 1.0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_end, 0, new_pos plus 1
    Let denom_pct be proc int_to_float from Arith with 100
    Return n divided by denom_pct
End Process

@Reasoning
Decode rgb() or rgba() into a freshly allocated color record.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Find the opening '(' after the prefix, read three rgb channels
separated by commas (with optional whitespace), optionally read a
trailing alpha, require a closing ')'.  Each channel uses
attr_color_read_rgb_channel which handles both integer (n/255) and
percentage (n%/100) forms.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(length).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on parse failure or allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "attr_decode_rgb_function" takes value_string as Integer, has_alpha as Integer returns Integer:
    Let len be proc string_length from StringCore with value_string
    Let prefix_len be 4
    If has_alpha is equal to 1:
        Set prefix_len to 5
    End If
    If prefix_len is greater than len:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let pos be prefix_len
    Let out_end be proc allocate from Layout with 8
    If out_end is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_end, 0, 0
    Let r_val be proc attr_color_read_rgb_channel with value_string, pos, len, out_end
    Set pos to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with out_end, 0
    If r_val is less than 0.0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with out_end
        Return 0
    End If
    Let pc1 be proc attr_color_expect_char with value_string, pos, len, 44
    If pc1 is less than 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with out_end
        Return 0
    End If
    Set pos to pc1
    Let g_val be proc attr_color_read_rgb_channel with value_string, pos, len, out_end
    Set pos to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with out_end, 0
    If g_val is less than 0.0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with out_end
        Return 0
    End If
    Let pc2 be proc attr_color_expect_char with value_string, pos, len, 44
    If pc2 is less than 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with out_end
        Return 0
    End If
    Set pos to pc2
    Let b_val be proc attr_color_read_rgb_channel with value_string, pos, len, out_end
    Set pos to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with out_end, 0
    If b_val is less than 0.0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with out_end
        Return 0
    End If
    Let alpha_val be 1.0
    If has_alpha is equal to 1:
        Let pc3 be proc attr_color_expect_char with value_string, pos, len, 44
        If pc3 is less than 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with out_end
            Return 0
        End If
        Set pos to pc3
        Let a_parsed be proc attr_color_read_alpha with value_string, pos, len, out_end
        Set pos to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with out_end, 0
        If a_parsed is less than 0.0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with out_end
            Return 0
        End If
        Set alpha_val to a_parsed
    End If
    Let pc_close be proc attr_color_expect_char with value_string, pos, len, 41
    proc deallocate from Layout with out_end
    If pc_close is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let rec be proc attr_color_rec_alloc
    If rec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc attr_color_rec_store with rec, ATTR_COLOR_REC_OFF_R, r_val
    proc attr_color_rec_store with rec, ATTR_COLOR_REC_OFF_G, g_val
    proc attr_color_rec_store with rec, ATTR_COLOR_REC_OFF_B, b_val
    proc attr_color_rec_store with rec, ATTR_COLOR_REC_OFF_A, alpha_val
    Return rec
End Process

@Reasoning
Decode hsl() or hsla() into a freshly allocated color record.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Parse the hue (degrees, no unit suffix required), then two percentage
channels for saturation and lightness, then optionally an alpha.
Construct an Hsl.ColorHsl and call Hsl.hsl_to_rgb to write the four
Float64 channels into a 32-byte buffer.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(length).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on parse failure or allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "attr_decode_hsl_function" takes value_string as Integer, has_alpha as Integer returns Integer:
    Let len be proc string_length from StringCore with value_string
    Let prefix_len be 4
    If has_alpha is equal to 1:
        Set prefix_len to 5
    End If
    If prefix_len is greater than len:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let pos be prefix_len
    Let out_end be proc allocate from Layout with 8
    If out_end is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with out_end, 0, 0
    Let after_ws_h be proc attr_color_skip_ws with value_string, pos, len
    Let hue be proc attr_color_read_number with value_string, after_ws_h, len, out_end
    Let new_h_pos be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with out_end, 0
    If new_h_pos is equal to after_ws_h:
        proc deallocate from Layout with out_end
        Return 0
    End If
    Set pos to new_h_pos
    Note: Consume optional "deg" suffix on the hue value.  CSS Color 4
    Note: accepts any of <number>, <number>deg as hue; we accept either.
    If (pos plus 2) is less than len:
        Let hch_d be proc string_char_at from StringCore with value_string, pos
        Let hch_e be proc string_char_at from StringCore with value_string, pos plus 1
        Let hch_g be proc string_char_at from StringCore with value_string, pos plus 2
        If hch_d is equal to 100:
            If hch_e is equal to 101:
                If hch_g is equal to 103:
                    Set pos to pos plus 3
                End If
            End If
        End If
    End If
    Let pc1 be proc attr_color_expect_char with value_string, pos, len, 44
    If pc1 is less than 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with out_end
        Return 0
    End If
    Set pos to pc1
    Let sat be proc attr_color_read_percent with value_string, pos, len, out_end
    Set pos to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with out_end, 0
    If sat is less than 0.0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with out_end
        Return 0
    End If
    Let pc2 be proc attr_color_expect_char with value_string, pos, len, 44
    If pc2 is less than 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with out_end
        Return 0
    End If
    Set pos to pc2
    Let light be proc attr_color_read_percent with value_string, pos, len, out_end
    Set pos to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with out_end, 0
    If light is less than 0.0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with out_end
        Return 0
    End If
    Let alpha_val be 1.0
    If has_alpha is equal to 1:
        Let pc3 be proc attr_color_expect_char with value_string, pos, len, 44
        If pc3 is less than 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with out_end
            Return 0
        End If
        Set pos to pc3
        Let a_parsed be proc attr_color_read_alpha with value_string, pos, len, out_end
        Set pos to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with out_end, 0
        If a_parsed is less than 0.0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with out_end
            Return 0
        End If
        Set alpha_val to a_parsed
    End If
    Let pc_close be proc attr_color_expect_char with value_string, pos, len, 41
    proc deallocate from Layout with out_end
    If pc_close is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let hsl_color be proc hsl_create from Hsl with hue, sat, light, alpha_val
    Let rec be proc allocate from Layout with ATTR_COLOR_REC_SIZE
    If rec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc hsl_to_rgb from Hsl with hsl_color, rec
    Return rec
End Process

@Reasoning
Decode a named CSS color identifier into a freshly allocated color
record via Palette.palette_lookup_by_name.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Allocate 32 bytes, call palette_lookup_by_name which writes (r, g, b,
1.0).  If the lookup misses, free the record and return 0.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(named-color table size).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on lookup miss or allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "attr_decode_named_color" takes value_string as Integer returns Integer:
    Let rec be proc allocate from Layout with ATTR_COLOR_REC_SIZE
    If rec is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let found be proc palette_lookup_by_name from Palette with value_string, rec
    If found is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with rec
        Return 0
    End If
    Return rec
End Process

@Reasoning
Public color-attribute parser.  Dispatches on the textual form, decodes
into a 32-byte (r, g, b, a) Float64 record, and wraps that record as
the payload of a TypedAttributeValue tagged ATTR_TYPE_COLOR.  The
original color space (HEX / RGB / RGBA / HSL / HSLA / NAMED) is
preserved in the unit slot.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
1. Check '#'-prefixed hex via attr_is_hex_color, then attr_decode_hex_color.
2. Check "rgb(" / "rgba(" / "hsl(" / "hsla(" prefixes (longer matches
   first) and dispatch to the corresponding decoder.
3. Fall through to attr_decode_named_color for bare identifiers.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(length).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on malformed input or allocation failure; otherwise the
caller owns the returned TypedAttributeValue and its 32-byte color
record payload.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "attr_parse_color" takes value_string as Integer returns Integer:
    If value_string is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let len be proc string_length from StringCore with value_string
    If len is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let is_hex be proc attr_is_hex_color with value_string
    If is_hex is equal to 1:
        Let rec_hex be proc attr_decode_hex_color with value_string
        If rec_hex is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Return proc typed_value_create with ATTR_TYPE_COLOR, rec_hex, ATTR_COLOR_SPACE_HEX
    End If
    Let rgba_prefix be proc string_starts_with from StringCore with value_string, "rgba("
    If rgba_prefix is equal to 1:
        Let rec_rgba be proc attr_decode_rgb_function with value_string, 1
        If rec_rgba is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Return proc typed_value_create with ATTR_TYPE_COLOR, rec_rgba, ATTR_COLOR_SPACE_RGBA
    End If
    Let rgb_prefix be proc string_starts_with from StringCore with value_string, "rgb("
    If rgb_prefix is equal to 1:
        Let rec_rgb be proc attr_decode_rgb_function with value_string, 0
        If rec_rgb is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Return proc typed_value_create with ATTR_TYPE_COLOR, rec_rgb, ATTR_COLOR_SPACE_RGB
    End If
    Let hsla_prefix be proc string_starts_with from StringCore with value_string, "hsla("
    If hsla_prefix is equal to 1:
        Let rec_hsla be proc attr_decode_hsl_function with value_string, 1
        If rec_hsla is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Return proc typed_value_create with ATTR_TYPE_COLOR, rec_hsla, ATTR_COLOR_SPACE_HSLA
    End If
    Let hsl_prefix be proc string_starts_with from StringCore with value_string, "hsl("
    If hsl_prefix is equal to 1:
        Let rec_hsl be proc attr_decode_hsl_function with value_string, 0
        If rec_hsl is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        Return proc typed_value_create with ATTR_TYPE_COLOR, rec_hsl, ATTR_COLOR_SPACE_HSL
    End If
    Let rec_named be proc attr_decode_named_color with value_string
    If rec_named is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc typed_value_create with ATTR_TYPE_COLOR, rec_named, ATTR_COLOR_SPACE_NAMED
End Process

@Reasoning
Recover the red channel (Float64 in [0, 1]) from a decoded color
TypedAttributeValue.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation
Load the bit-cast Float at offset 0 of the payload record.
@End Implementation
@Performance_Hints
O(1).
@End Performance_Hints
@Security_Scope
Returns 0.0 for null or non-color typed values.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "typed_value_color_get_r" takes value as Integer returns Float:
    If value is equal to 0:
        Return 0.0
    End If
    Let tag be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with value, TYPED_VALUE_OFF_TYPE
    If tag is not equal to ATTR_TYPE_COLOR:
        Return 0.0
    End If
    Let rec be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with value, TYPED_VALUE_OFF_PAYLOAD
    If rec is equal to 0:
        Return 0.0
    End If
    Let bits be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with rec, ATTR_COLOR_REC_OFF_R
    Return proc bits_to_float from Hsl with bits
End Process

